  "prompt": "What is a programmable shifter?",
  "response": "A programmable shifter, also known as an electronic shifter or smart shifter, is a device used in automotive or motorcycle applications that allows for automated or customized gear shifting. Unlike traditional manual transmission shifters, programmable shifters can be configured to:\n\n1. Automatically shift gears based on pre-set parameters\n2. Allow custom shift points and patterns\n3. Provide different shift modes (e.g., comfort, sport, economy)\n4. Enable precise and quick gear changes\n5. Integrate with vehicle performance systems\n\nThese shifters are commonly used in performance vehicles, racing cars, and high-end motorcycles to optimize transmission performance and driving experience.",
